-- Migration 030: Update platform consent templates with complete, compliant content
-- IMPORTANT: These templates should be reviewed by a licensed healthcare attorney
-- before use in production. They are provided as a strong starting point only.

-- Update HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices
UPDATE consent_templates
SET
  version = 2,
  content_markdown = E'## Notice of Privacy Practices\n\n**Effective Date:** January 1, 2025\n\nThis Notice of Privacy Practices ("Notice") describes how your provider and their practice ("we," "us," "our") may use and disclose your protected health information ("PHI") and how you can access this information. **Please read this Notice carefully before signing.**\n\nWe are required by law to:\n- Maintain the privacy of your PHI\n- Provide you with this Notice of our legal duties and privacy practices\n- Follow the terms of the Notice currently in effect\n- Notify you in the event of a breach of your unsecured PHI\n\n---\n\n### 1. How We May Use and Disclose Your Health Information\n\n**Treatment.** We may use and disclose your PHI to provide, coordinate, or manage your healthcare and related services. This includes sharing information with other healthcare providers involved in your care.\n\n**Payment.** We may use and disclose your PHI to obtain payment for services provided to you. This includes submitting claims to insurance companies, Medicare, Medicaid, or other payers, and responding to coverage inquiries.\n\n**Healthcare Operations.** We may use and disclose your PHI for our internal operations, including quality assessment, provider training, accreditation, legal and auditing functions, and business management.\n\n**Appointment Reminders.** We may contact you to remind you of upcoming appointments or to follow up on your care.\n\n**Treatment Alternatives.** We may use and disclose your PHI to tell you about treatment alternatives or health-related products and services that may be of interest to you.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Uses and Disclosures That May Be Made Without Your Authorization\n\nIn certain situations, we are permitted or required by law to use or disclose your PHI without your written authorization:\n\n- **Public Health Activities:** Reporting disease, injury, or disability as required by public health authorities.\n- **Health Oversight Activities:** Disclosures to government agencies for audits, inspections, or investigations.\n- **Judicial and Administrative Proceedings:** In response to a court order, subpoena, or other lawful process.\n- **Law Enforcement:** To comply with reporting requirements under law, or in response to a valid law enforcement request.\n- **Serious Threats to Health or Safety:** To prevent or lessen a serious and imminent threat to the health or safety of a person or the public.\n- **Workers'' Compensation:** As authorized by and to the extent necessary to comply with workers'' compensation laws.\n- **Required by Law:** Any other use or disclosure required by applicable federal or state law.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Uses and Disclosures Requiring Your Written Authorization\n\nThe following uses and disclosures will be made only with your written authorization:\n\n- Most uses and disclosures of **psychotherapy notes**\n- Uses and disclosures of PHI for **marketing purposes**\n- Sales of your PHI\n- Any use or disclosure not described in this Notice\n\nYou may revoke any authorization you have given at any time, in writing. Revocation will not affect any actions taken in reliance on your prior authorization.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Your Rights Regarding Your Health Information\n\n**Right to Access.** You have the right to inspect and receive a copy of your PHI that we maintain in a designated record set. Requests must be submitted in writing. We may charge a reasonable fee for copies. We will respond within 30 days.\n\n**Right to Request Amendment.** You have the right to request that we amend your PHI if you believe it is incorrect or incomplete. We may deny your request under certain circumstances and will explain the reason in writing.\n\n**Right to an Accounting of Disclosures.** You have the right to request a list of certain disclosures of your PHI made during the six years prior to your request. This does not include disclosures for treatment, payment, or healthcare operations.\n\n**Right to Request Restrictions.** You have the right to request restrictions on certain uses and disclosures of your PHI. We are not required to agree to your request, except we must agree to restrict disclosures to your health plan if you pay for the service entirely out of pocket and the disclosure is not required by law.\n\n**Right to Request Confidential Communications.** You have the right to request that we communicate with you about your health matters in a certain way or at a certain location. We will accommodate reasonable requests.\n\n**Right to a Paper Copy of This Notice.** You have the right to receive a paper copy of this Notice upon request, even if you agreed to receive it electronically.\n\n**Right to Be Notified of a Breach.** You have the right to receive notification if there is a breach of your unsecured PHI.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Our Duties\n\nWe are required by law to maintain the privacy of your PHI and to provide you with this Notice. We are required to abide by the terms of the Notice currently in effect. We reserve the right to change our privacy practices and the terms of this Notice at any time, provided such changes are permitted by applicable law. Changes will apply to PHI already held by us as well as information we receive in the future. We will post the current Notice in the patient portal.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How to File a Complaint\n\nIf you believe your privacy rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with us or with the Secretary of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. To file a complaint with us, contact your provider directly through this portal. **We will not retaliate against you for filing a complaint.**\n\nTo file a complaint with the Secretary of HHS:\n**Office for Civil Rights, U.S. Department of Health and Human Services**\n200 Independence Avenue, S.W., Washington, D.C. 20201\n[www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy](https://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Contact Information\n\nFor questions about this Notice or to exercise any of your rights, please contact your provider directly through the patient portal messaging system.\n\n---\n\n*By acknowledging this Notice, you confirm that you have received and had the opportunity to review our Notice of Privacy Practices. Acknowledgment of this Notice is not a condition of treatment.*',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE document_type = 'hipaa_notice'
  AND practitioner_id IS NULL;

-- Update Informed Consent for Telehealth Services
UPDATE consent_templates
SET
  version = 2,
  content_markdown = E'## Informed Consent for Telehealth Services\n\n**Please read this consent carefully. By signing below, you are agreeing to receive healthcare services via telehealth.**\n\n---\n\n### 1. What Is Telehealth?\n\nTelehealth is the delivery of healthcare services — including evaluation, diagnosis, consultation, treatment, and patient education — through electronic communications when the provider and patient are not in the same physical location. Telehealth may include:\n\n- Video consultations (synchronous audio/video)\n- Secure asynchronous messaging through the patient portal\n- Electronic transmission of medical records, images, and lab results\n- Remote monitoring and review of health data\n\n---\n\n### 2. Technology and Platform\n\nYour provider uses a HIPAA-compliant telehealth platform with encryption and access controls to protect your health information. You are responsible for ensuring that you have a private, secure environment during telehealth sessions and that your device and internet connection are suitable for video communication.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Functional and Integrative Medicine Approach\n\nYour provider practices functional and/or integrative medicine, which focuses on identifying and addressing the root causes of health conditions. Care may include:\n\n- Comprehensive health history and intake evaluation\n- Advanced laboratory testing and interpretation (including specialty labs such as DUTCH hormone panels, microbiome analysis, nutrient testing)\n- Personalized nutrition and lifestyle recommendations\n- Targeted supplementation protocols\n- Mind-body interventions\n- Coordination with other healthcare providers\n\n**Important:** Functional and integrative medicine recommendations are intended to complement, not replace, conventional medical care. If you are experiencing an emergency or acute illness, you should contact 911 or go to your nearest emergency room.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Benefits of Telehealth\n\n- Convenient access to specialized care without travel\n- Access to providers who may not be available locally\n- Ability to receive care from the comfort of your home\n- Continuity of care between in-person visits\n- Secure access to your health records and lab results\n\n---\n\n### 5. Risks and Limitations of Telehealth\n\nI understand that telehealth has potential limitations, including but not limited to:\n\n- **Technical failures:** Poor internet connectivity, equipment malfunction, or software issues may interrupt or prevent a session. If this occurs, my provider will contact me by phone to continue care or reschedule.\n- **Limitations of remote assessment:** My provider cannot perform a physical examination and may have limited ability to assess certain conditions compared to an in-person visit. Some conditions may require in-person evaluation.\n- **Privacy risks:** Although all reasonable precautions are taken, electronic communications carry a risk of interception. I should use a private network and location during all telehealth sessions.\n- **Prescribing limitations:** Not all medications can be prescribed via telehealth. Certain controlled substances require in-person evaluation under applicable law.\n- **Emergency limitations:** Telehealth is not appropriate for medical emergencies. In a life-threatening situation, I should call 911 immediately.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Emergency Procedures\n\nIn the event of a medical emergency during a telehealth session, my provider will direct me to call 911 or go to the nearest emergency room. I understand I should always have access to emergency services and provide my provider with a local contact person and address in case of emergency.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Privacy and Confidentiality\n\nAll telehealth communications are subject to the same confidentiality protections as in-person visits and are governed by HIPAA and applicable state laws. Sessions will not be recorded by my provider without my separate written consent. I agree not to record sessions without my provider''s explicit consent.\n\n---\n\n### 8. State Licensure and Interstate Practice\n\nMy provider is licensed to practice in specific states. I understand that I must be physically located in a state where my provider is licensed at the time of each telehealth visit. If I relocate, I agree to notify my provider before my next appointment, as this may affect my provider''s ability to continue treating me.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Informed Consent and Shared Decision-Making\n\nI understand that:\n\n1. I have been given the opportunity to ask questions about telehealth services, and my questions have been answered to my satisfaction.\n2. My participation in telehealth services is voluntary.\n3. I have the right to withhold or withdraw consent at any time without affecting my right to future care.\n4. To withdraw consent, I must notify my provider in writing through the patient portal.\n5. My provider may determine that telehealth is not appropriate for my condition and may refer me for in-person care.\n6. I am responsible for providing accurate and complete health information to support safe and effective care.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Supplement and Lifestyle Recommendations\n\nI understand that supplement protocols and lifestyle interventions recommended by my provider are based on available research and clinical judgment. I acknowledge that:\n\n- Dietary supplements are not FDA-approved to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.\n- I will inform my provider of all medications and supplements I currently take to avoid potential interactions.\n- I accept responsibility for following recommendations safely and will report any adverse reactions promptly.\n\n---\n\n### 11. Financial Responsibility\n\nI understand that telehealth services may or may not be covered by my insurance plan. I accept financial responsibility for any services not covered by insurance. My provider''s billing policies will be explained separately.\n\n---\n\n### 12. Acknowledgment\n\nBy signing this consent, I confirm that:\n\n- I have read and understood this Informed Consent for Telehealth Services.\n- I have had the opportunity to ask questions.\n- I voluntarily consent to receive healthcare services via telehealth.\n- I understand the benefits, risks, and limitations described above.\n- I am the patient or the legally authorized representative of the patient named in this record.',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE document_type = 'treatment_consent'
  AND practitioner_id IS NULL;
